3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper involves the use of deep learning-based optic cup segmentation and sparse learning-based CDR computation, which suggests that it may be relevant to the machine learning community. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper involves the analysis of retinal images, which may be relevant to the information retrieval community. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with retinal image processing and analysis, which may be relevant to the multimedia community.
